        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is a white-label SEO tool?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A white-label SEO tool is software or a service that an agency resells under its own brand. The client sees the agency's logo on reports, dashboards, or content — they never see the underlying vendor. White-label arrangements turn fulfillment into margin: the agency charges retail and pays wholesale, keeping the spread without doing the production work in-house.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can small agencies afford white-label SEO software?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Tools like theStacc start at $99/mo wholesale and resell at $399 to $999, leaving 75 to 90 percent gross margin even on a single client. Reporting tools like DashThis and AgencyAnalytics start under $50. The barrier is not cost — it is picking tools that produce a deliverable clients can actually see, not just dashboards.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do white-label SEO tools include client reporting?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Most do. SE Ranking, BrightLocal, AgencyAnalytics, and DashThis all generate branded PDF or live-link reports with the agency logo and color scheme. Vendasta and Semrush Agency Growth Kit bundle reporting with broader fulfillment. theStacc ships content under your brand and reports through whichever analytics tool you already use.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the best white-label SEO tool for local businesses?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>BrightLocal is the local SEO incumbent — citation building, rank tracking, GBP audits all under your brand. Vendasta is broader and bundles reputation management. For agencies that want to resell local content alongside GBP work, theStacc covers both content and GBP automation in one white-label stack.</p></div></div>
